column9: Lussvale is a Rangelands sheep and cattle station located approximately 110km north of Bollon and 110km south of Mitchell, Queensland. The project will manage the timing and the extent of grazing to promote the regeneration of even-aged permanent native forests, specifically by progressive implementation of increased internal paddocks to facilitate rotational grazing, additional watering points and targeted exclusion fencing. In addition to remote sensing by Climate Friendly and CIBO Labs, as well as on-ground management to closely monitor safe grazing levels to promote of the regeneration of native forest for the project.
